  "prompt": "Which is a suitable solar panel installation provider near San Gabriel, California CA?",
  "response": "When looking for a suitable solar panel installation provider near San Gabriel, California, it's important to consider factors such as reputation, experience, customer reviews, and the range of services offered. Here are a few highly-rated providers in the area:\n\n1. **SunPower by Sea Bright Solar**:\n   - **Location**: Nearby in Los Angeles\n   - **Why Choose Them**: SunPower is known for its high-efficiency solar panels and excellent customer service. Sea Bright Solar has a strong reputation in the region for quality installations and comprehensive services.\n\n2. **Solar Optimum**:\n   - **Location**: With offices in the San Gabriel Valley\n   - **Why Choose Them**: Solar Optimum is well-regarded for its custom solar solutions and has a strong presence in Southern California. They offer a full suite of services from consultation to installation and maintenance.\n\n3. **Titan Solar Power**:\n   - **Location**: Serving the San Gabriel area\n   - **Why Choose Them**: Titan Solar Power is praised for its quick and efficient installations, competitive pricing, and excellent customer support. They are known for their professionalism and high-quality workmanship.\n\n4. **PetersenDean**:\n   - **Location**: Nearby in the Greater Los Angeles area\n   - **Why Choose Them**: PetersenDean has been in the solar industry for many years and offers a wide range of services including solar, roofing, and energy efficiency solutions. They are known for their reliable installations and good warranty options.\n\nBefore making a final decision, it's recommended to:\n- **Get multiple quotes**: Compare pricing and services from at least three different providers.\n- **Check reviews and ratings**: Look at customer feedback on platforms like Yelp, Google Reviews, and the Better Business Bureau.\n- **Verify certifications and licenses**: Ensure the company is properly licensed and certified to operate in California.\n- **Ask about warranties and maintenance**: Understand what kind of warranty is offered on the solar panels and the installation work, as well as what maintenance services are available.\n\nBy doing your due diligence, you can find a solar panel installation provider that best meets your needs and ensures a successful transition to solar energy.",
